Any heater with an unshielded flame needs a mandatory supply of fresh air. If you use them in closed rooms they eventually consume all oxygen and then emit carbon monoxide due to unclean combustion. CO is scentless and invisible and therefore absolutely deadly. You just get tired and have no chance to react or save yourself. I am shocked that the boys already had burning eyes which is a very close call there! If they hadn't the vent in the ceilling they might have got some serious poisoning.

Guys please keep the doors halfway open all times!
